# Live execution visibility (mandatory)

## Portal SoT

- `src/content/execution-runtime.json` (canonical)
- `src/contracts/` — shared schemas (no duplicate runtime types)
- API: `GET/PATCH /api/execution-runtime`
- UI: `/operations/live` (poll 8s)

## Cursor progress (every phase change + during long work)

```bash
npm run execution:phase -- --phase planning --task "..." --subsystem ... --reasoning "..." --confidence 0.85 --next "..."
npm run execution:heartbeat   # every 5–15s during active work
npm run execution:waiting-review -- --pending 5   # when diff awaits Apply
npm run execution:heal        # self-healing: typecheck, build, deploy:validate
```

Terminal must echo: `[PHASE] summary` (script does this).

## Status values

`idle | planning | analyzing | coding | validating | reviewing | deploying | blocked | waiting_approval | waiting_review | completed`

## After owner Apply/Accept

Resume autonomously — update phase to `coding` or `validating`, **no "what next?"**

## Do NOT

- Stream raw chain-of-thought
- Fake heartbeat without real work
- Spam feed with log dumps (use runtime state + feed:append at milestones)

## Commit runtime state

Include `execution-runtime-state.json` in portal commits at cycle end (`validating` → `deploying` → `completed`).
